The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 March is 40,759 (4,717.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 March, there were 296 new confirmed cases (34.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 February, there were 494 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 40% (198 fewer cases).
